      • get

        javax.ws.rs.core.Response get(org.apache.jena.query.Query query,
                              List<URI> defaultGraphUris,
                              List<URI> namedGraphUris)
        Handles GET query request and returns result as response
        Parameters:
        query - the submitted SPARQL query
        defaultGraphUris - default graph URI
        namedGraphUris - named graph URI
        Returns:
        result response (in one of the representation variants)
        See Also:
        2.1.1 query via GET

      • post

        javax.ws.rs.core.Response post(String queryString,
                               String updateString,
                               List<URI> defaultGraphUris,
                               List<URI> namedGraphUris,
                               List<URI> usingGraphUris,
                               List<URI> usingNamedGraphUris)
        Handles URL-encoded POST query request and returns result as response. Query and UpdateRequest would be more appropriate form parameter types, but the injection provider does not have access to request entity or form parameters.
        Parameters:
        queryString - submitted SPARQL query string
        updateString - submitted SPARQL update string
        defaultGraphUris - default graph URI
        namedGraphUris - named graph URI
        usingGraphUris - default graph URI
        usingNamedGraphUris - named graph URI
        Returns:
        result response (in one of the representation variants)
        See Also:
        2.1.2 query via POST with URL-encoded parameters, 2.2.1 update via POST with URL-encoded parameters

      • post

        javax.ws.rs.core.Response post(org.apache.jena.query.Query query,
                               List<URI> defaultGraphUris,

        Handles direct POST query request and returns result as response
        Parameters:
        query - the submitted SPARQL query
        defaultGraphUris - default graph URI

        Returns:
        result response (in one of the representation variants)
        See Also:
        2.1.3 query via POST directly

      • post

        javax.ws.rs.core.Response post(org.apache.jena.update.UpdateRequest update,
                               List<URI> usingGraphUris,
                               List<URI> usingNamedGraphUris)
        Handles direct POST update request and returns result as response
        Parameters:
        update - update request (possibly multiple operations)
        usingGraphUris - default graph URI
        usingNamedGraphUris - named graph URI
        Returns:
        success or failure response
        See Also:
        2.2.2 update via POST directly
